04/01/2007
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Government spokesman Christodoulos Pashiardes said on Wednesday (January 3rd) that Nicosia is ready to negotiate and resolve the Cyprus problem this year. Pashiardes added that elections in Turkey should not jeopardise efforts to advance the settlement process, especially implementation of the July 2006 framework agreement, which envisions negotiations on concrete quality of life issues. (CNA - 03/01/07)
